                            <comment id="13536763" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 20 Dec 2012 04:27:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at ExportSnapshot.java:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    FileSystem outputFs = FileSystem.get(outputRoot.toUri(), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Configuration());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can we use getConf() in place of &apos;new Configuration()&apos; ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;in case of shared instead&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can you explain how shared mapper comes about ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13538454" author="jmhsieh" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2012 21:54:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Can you explain how shared mapper comes about ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe this is a hadoop 1 vs hadoop 2 unit test problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13539963" author="mbertozzi" created="Thu, 27 Dec 2012 14:12:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;changes between hadoop 1 and 2.&lt;br/&gt;
and since in the test, the mappers seems running in the same jvm&lt;br/&gt;
fs.close() called by the mapper interferes with the one used by the main().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13539979" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Dec 2012 15:12:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see.&lt;br/&gt;
What do you think about my other comment w.r.t. &apos;new Configuration()&apos; ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540033" author="mbertozzi" created="Thu, 27 Dec 2012 16:52:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sorry Ted, I tend to forget to reply, to comments/nits/suggestions that I agree with, and I&apos;m going change the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, you&apos;re right.&lt;br/&gt;
The configuration doesn&apos;t matter since the user should specify a qualified path hdfs://cluster2&lt;br/&gt;
and in case of unqualified path, you&apos;ve an &quot;unexpected&quot; result in both case. but at least using the getConf()&lt;br/&gt;
you&apos;re sure that you get all your config (HBaseConfig is used) and maybe your fs.default.name is inside one of those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540039" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Dec 2012 17:00:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick response.&lt;br/&gt;
+1 on second patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
